cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with improving the perceptual quality of images using CNN-based super-resolution techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel attention mechanism based on human visual perception, which involves designing a spatial attention map. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves training CNNs, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a new technique to improve the performance of loss metrics, which may also fall under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
